A wonderful novel inspired by the true stories of the female footballing legends who rose to fame during the women’s #football boom of WW1

“They can take our ball, but they can never stop the game…”

A hundred years before the Lionesses, Lily Parr, Alice Woods and their teammates were proudly playing their beloved, exciting and skilful game.

They can take our ball, but they can never stop the game.

As men were sent to fight in the war, women and girls took their place in munitions factories. Football became a favourite pastime and, before long, they were creating all-female sides and playing public matches to sell-out crowds, overshadowing the men's football. Despite drawing crowds of 50,000, women's football was outlawed by the Football Association in 1921, who deemed it 'unsuitable for females'.

This is the incredible story of these amazing women.

📚NEW BOOKS …📚

Good morning all. After work yesterday, I spend a couple of hours with my family having a walk, visiting @toppingsely & we had a nice drink out too. I don’t know if it’s odd but I love sitting in a cafe with a hot drink & chatting whilst it’s getting dusky & dark outside. Anyhow, it was a nice afternoon. 

The husband was very generous & treated us all to a new book yesterday. I did ask whether you preferred to see our new books in my stories or a post, stories won but I’m showing it in a post too as I kinda fancy it! 🙈😂 I have shared the synopsis too so have a swipe ➡️

For me: The Beautiful Dead - after recently reading & enjoying Exit by the same author, I thought I would check out her other reads & I loved the synopsis of this one. I think it’s one I can pass on to the husband also. 

For the husband: Moriarty -  he spent some time looking around & this one caught his eye. 

For the 9 year old: Our Beautiful Game - our ‘Matilda’ said she normally avoided books based in the war as they make her sad but she wanted to give this one a try as it sounded interesting. 

For the 6 year old: Christmas Sparkle collection - neither of my girls have read many of the Rainbow Magic books but this one stood out to my little bookworm yesterday, I think the festive aspect won her over. 

So that’s the haul & I wish you all a fabulous Sunday however you’re spending it. 💜

글로벌 스포츠 브랜드 나이키(Nike)가 브랜드 최대 명절로 꼽히는 '에어맥스 데이(Air Max Day)'를 맞아 브랜드의 근간이 된 언더그라운드 음악에 경의를 표하는 깜짝 라디오 방송을 진행했습니다.
나이키와 라디오라니... 뭔가 이질적이죠?? ㅎㅎ 
1987년 3월 26일 첫 출시된 나이키의 시그니처 운동화인 에어맥스의 탄생을 기념하는 날인 만큼, 아주 고전적인 매체 '라디오'를 통해 브랜드의 정신을 알리고자 했다고 합니다. 
라디오를 거의 듣지 않는 젊은 세대에게 새로운 아티스트와 에어맥스를 독특하고 기억에 남는 방법으로 연결시킨 나이키의 '온에어맥스' 캠페인! 뭘해도 힙한 나이키입니다!

Mariana Bracetti is believed to have been the woman who crafted the first Puerto Rican flag, an earlier version of the one we know today. Bracetti was an independence movement leader in the 1860s and a key protagonist of the Grito de Lares, a failed revolt in the town of Lares that declared the first Puerto Rican republic in 1868. She was arrested and released a few months later, after she was granted amnesty from the Spanish government. Before the Grito de Lares, she was nicknamed “Brazo de oro” because of her sewing abilities and was appointed leader of the Lares Revolutionary Council. Her original Puerto Rican flag – known to many as the Bandera Revolucionaria – belongs to the University of Puerto Rico today.

After #Nike enlisted a biological man to advertise a #bra and #leggings, many people expressed their disapproval by leaving comments on Nike's #Instagram account. Earlier this week, Autogynephiliac #DylanMulvaney, who identifies as a #transgender 'woman', posted content in which he was sporting the women's apparel: "Home for a moment and leaning into cozy workout wear life with @NikeWomen‘s newest #Zenvy leggings and Alate bra! They’re so comfortable and buttery soft, perfect for workouts and everyday wear! #feelyourall #teamnike #NikePartner," #Mulvaney wrote in an Instagram post that has been labeled as a paid partnership...

Nike's move to have a man advertise women's clothing sparked backlash, with people making their disapproval known on Nike's Instagram page.

"I have five grandsons that I won’t be buying Nike products for anymore. I'll buy from companies that support women," one person wrote in a comment on a Nike post advertising a shoe.

"I don't support misogyny or delusions. No more Nike for me," someone else wrote.

"I am never buying your products again! Go woke go broke!" another commenter declared.

Nike dropped a message of its own in the comments section, declaring, "You are an essential component to the success of your community! The company wrote that, "Hate speech, bullying, or other behaviors that are not in the spirit of a diverse and inclusive community will be deleted."

Anheuser-Busch also recently came under heavy criticism for having Mulvaney advertise #BudLight and for sending Mulvaney a beer can with his face on it.

“나이키에서도 처음하는 행사예요”
마케팅담당자께서 제안주셨을때 많은 감정이 피어올랐다
올해 1월 만다라트에 써두었던 메가브랜드와의 협업이 이루어지는 순간이었다
운동인 주변에는 러너가 워낙 많아서 모르지만 사실 달리기에 부담같는 사람들이 아주 많다 
빨리 달려야 할 것 같아서, 부상이 생길까봐 저어한다
반대로 걸으면 운동이 되나 하는 경우도 많다 
이런 모든 의구심과 장벽을 해소해서 멋진 행사를 만들고 싶어 미팅이후 계속 답사하고 계속 걸으면서 그림을 그렸다
행사 시간대에 그 장소의 온도, 바람, 해가 비치는 방향, 새들의 지저귐 정도, 외부 운동하는 일반일들, 보이는 경치 등등
있는 그대로의 환경이 줄 수 있는 최적의 컨디션을 확보하고 싶었다
근데 결국 비가 왔다 하핫
하지만 거의 노쇼없이 참석을 해주셨고, 답사 할때마다 사실은 그날 그날의 선물같은 자연과 컨디션이 달랐기에 힘을 냈다
-
헤드셋을 끼고 내가 플레이하는 음악, 이야기를 공유하며 마인드풀워킹을 시작했다

Get you a girl who can be both: A baddie and a goof. I turned 33 on March 29 and reached my anniversary of mixed martial arts on April 2nd. Can I get an amen! These are the blessed 33 things I’ve learned, and I hope that you do too:
—
1) Honor the process.
2) Mental wellness is a martial art: Train your brain as much as your body.
3) Commitment is sexy.
4) Doing the work is also very, very sexy.
5) Flowers need sun, water, and air. So do you to grow in your own time.
6) Everything always works out for you even if it doesn’t seem like it on the outside.
7) Find your people, the ones who get your weird and your wins.
8) Not everything is a competition. It’s a learning lesson.
9) Strike when the iron is hot. The moment matters.
10) The art of war is the art of peace.
11) With anything in life, it’s important to know your style and own it from the bones.
12) Being teachable is more attractive than being right.
13) Everyone operates at their own speed, so drive accordingly.
14) Be kind is badass.
15) Allow life to surprise you as you stay the course.
16) Forgive, but don’t forget.
17) “Thank you” is “I love you” too.
18) You are your biggest cheerleader.
19) Passion is non-negotiable when it comes to true purpose.
20) Find small goals to stay engaged in the big one.
21) Expertise comes in the most unlikeliest of places.
22) Stay grateful. Gratitude is magnitude.
23) Plan a solo artist date once a week to remind yourself that productivity includes pleasure.
24) Nature is your friend. And low-key free therapist.
25) Move based on your joy not other people’s judgment.
26) Time is your most finite resource.
27) Intuition is never wrong. Follow the feeling with your entire being.
28) Manifestation only works if you work.
29) Never let anyone make you feel inferior, period.
30) If luck is preparation meeting opportunity, then always stay ready.
31) Never forget where you came from.
32) The sword is only as good as its master.
33) Greatness is earned. There’s always a price to pay: Attention.
—

LIFE LATELY//: When it comes to my wellness and the routines I’m trying to cultivate, I’ve been very intentional about the ways in which I can find some softness in the moments.
.
.
Our wellness is so intersectional… and impacts how we feel. This week I had the opportunity to help others lean into the softness of it all and slow it all down. Slow movements, deep breaths and stillness was the theme. We worked through, tight hips, sore shoulders and met and embraced our bodies with kindness and compassion… because meeting yourself where you are at is such a beautiful thing. 
.
.
Still smiling from teaching at Nike Style Lounge NYC. Thank you @nikewomen for providing me with an opportunity to share this practice. A practice that celebrates the beauty of softness, slowing down, resting. A practice that reminds us our bodies are our friends and treating ourselves with compassion is the most liberating thing we can do.

This project has taken over the internet. What an incredible feeling this has been. 

This is how we celebrated International Women’s Month #feelyourall @nikewomen @native_women_running

Half day wellness retreat with @nike and @rebelsport
We condensed our retreat into a morning in Sydney & the turn-out was beyond anything I could have imagined! MY BESTIE CAME TOO SO MY YEAR IS NOW COMPLETE. ✔️ ✔️ 

Everyone that came was gifted my favourite items from the new Nike range (actually in love with the chocolate Nike Zenvy leggings and the crop of my dreams).

I ran them through a juicy, twisty, challenging yoga flow, breathwork & meditation. 🧘🏽‍♀️ 

May have personally gotten a little emotional talking about what #feelyourall means to me

(See 👇🏽 for what Feel Your All means to me)

The guests then moved into the next room where Brit & I presented WFPB* on-the-go snacks & had an in-depth chat about the necessity of being prepared in order to fuel your training, busy life and physical & mental health

*Whole Food Plant Based 🥙 🌱🌵

The retreat closed with 1HR of meditative dance, silent-disco style. A room of women, letting go of fears of being seen, letting our hair out and shimmying, laughing, crying until our smiling muscles could no longer keep up.

FEEL YOUR ALL.🌞
To me, this phrase perfectly describes the way I live life.
To be fully present in each moment makes it possible for you to feel your all.
If you’re stuck worrying about the past or fretting the future - your mind is not capable of embracing the present moment.

To be fully present is a HARD TASK. 
It is no simple, easy feat.

In fact, I have been working on it for years & work on it every day.
I have learnt the best way to support this journey is to NOURISH yourself through every facet.

Nourish your brain with optimal sleep.

Nourish your gut, energy, & immune system with diverse nutrition.

Nourish your mental health with meditation/yoga/time alone.

Nourish your body with plenty of movement & recovery.

As you can see, all of these concept’s feed into one another, so start small& slowly work up. 

Somewhere along the line, you’ll look back with GRATEFULNESS that you chose to start this journey.

PAUSE.
Put down your devices.
Take a few slow breaths.
Name 3 things you’re grateful for.
Name 3 things around you that you consider beautiful or joyful

An accurate depiction of me thinking about what I want to program in the next Hypertrophy Phase 🤔

@boltchicago takes its athletes through Linear Periodization. Linear Periodization is where you increase intensity and decrease volume over a period of time. 

There are 4 phases in this program:

⚡️ Hypertrophy/Muscle Endurance
⚡️ Basic Strength
⚡️ Power

Linear Periodization is great for beginners and advanced athletes alike who want to build a solid strength foundation. 

It’s a powerful tool for breaking plateaus and almost always guarantees better outcomes long term 👌

Stop exercising and start training with a purpose! See you in class 💪

Hoy la @ligabbvamxfemenil en conjunto con @nike anunciaron una alianza histórica para el futbol femenino en México.

La Liga Femenil tendrá a su primer patrocinador exclusivo a partir del Torneo Clausura 2023.

⚽️ De acuerdo con el comunicado publicado en el sitio web de La Liga Mx Femenil, la marca Nike confeccionará un balón de uso exclusivo para el balompié femenil de México.

⚽️El patrocinio busca apostar al desarrollo futbolístico de mujeres y niñas tal como se hizo con la @nwsl y la @barclayswsl que son dos de las Ligas más importantes a nivel mundial.

@m_guti_b destacó la importancia de esta alianza que promueve el desarrollo integral de las jugadoras en México: “Para ser una Liga autosustentable, necesitamos de marcas con los mismos valores que tiene la Liga BBVA MX Femenil para mantenernos auténticos en nuestro camino".

Her PerSOLEna:

"I like to walk around in them. They're very easy and comfortable to put on. And they're very practical. I'm on my feet all day, so I just want to be comfortable walking around the city. And they go with everything because the colors are neutral. They are my go-to work shoes!"

In a pinned comment to one of NIKE’s Instagram posts, the company responded to the barrage of people announcing they would be abandoning the brand for good.

“You are an essential component to the success of your community! We welcome comments that contribute to a positive and constructive discussion: Be kind. Be inclusive. Encourage each other. As Breitbart News reported this week, NIKE Women selected Dylan Mulvaney to sell women’s sports bras and leggings despite being a man.

“Home for a moment and leaning into cozy workout wear life with @nikewomen ‘s newest Zenvy leggings and Alate bra! They’re so comfortable and buttery soft, perfect for workouts and everyday wear! #feelyourall #teamnike #nikepartner,” Mulvaney said when announcing the new deal on Instagram. Customers responded by vowing to boycott the sports apparel giant and said the selection of Dylan Mulvaney contributes to the erasure of women. Female athletes are also weighing in on the situation.

“It’s so frustrating. We take two steps forward with World Athletics and Swim England protecting women’s sport and then Nike does this,” Olympic swimmer Sharron Davies told Dan Wootton Tonight on GB News.

“The ad feels like a parody of what women are. In the past, it was always seen as an insult to say ‘run like a girl,’ and here we’ve got someone behaving in a way that’s very unsporty and very unathletic. And it’s so frustrating when only 1% of the USA sponsorship dollar goes to females in sport. That Nike would do this feels like a kick in the teeth,” she added.

This chapter is called, “Rebirth.” It’s my birthday today. It’s a time of reflection and recommitment to the ethos and events of the past year that changed my life, especially with the most epic campaign I could ever ask for, @nikewomen @nike Feel Your All. My mom is very proud.
—
Winning the day one by one, I took on an unorthodox entry level of mixed martial arts to understand and actualize my sense of happiness. My wholeness. I’ve never felt more completely myself than when I hold a staff, sword, shield, and other fun tactical things that awaken the power within. I must have been hiding for a while for big magic had to fight itself through me. I’ve meant it when I’ve said that martial arts saved me from myself, battling anxiety about who I was and what I wanted, to be driven by purpose instead of pretend. Martial arts is life. I understand it as a warrior and I always will.
—

I judge less to feel more. I thank more to love much, much more. No limits. Just kisses from the stars and the little me who stubbornly held onto the hopes and dreams that the adult me is tasked to carry out to fulfillment for both of us. For all of us. You need to keep moving because the world needs you. You need you. Never, ever give up on yourself.
—

Get you a girl who can be both: A baddie and a goof. I turned 33 on March 29 and reached my anniversary of mixed martial arts on April 2nd. Can I get an amen! These are the blessed 33 things I’ve learned, and I hope that you do too:
—
1) Honor the process.
2) Mental wellness is a martial art: Train your brain as much as your body.
3) Commitment is sexy.
4) Doing the work is also very, very sexy.
5) Flowers need sun, water, and air. So do you to grow in your own time.
6) Everything always works out for you even if it doesn’t seem like it on the outside.
7) Find your people, the ones who get your weird and your wins.
8) Not everything is a competition. It’s a learning lesson.
9) Strike when the iron is hot. The moment matters.
10) The art of war is the art of peace.
11) With anything in life, it’s important to know your style and own it from the bones.
12) Being teachable is more attractive than being right.
13) Everyone operates at their own speed, so drive accordingly.
14) Be kind is badass.
15) Allow life to surprise you as you stay the course.
16) Forgive, but don’t forget.
17) “Thank you” is “I love you” too.
18) You are your biggest cheerleader.
19) Passion is non-negotiable when it comes to true purpose.
20) Find small goals to stay engaged in the big one.
21) Expertise comes in the most unlikeliest of places.
22) Stay grateful. Gratitude is magnitude.
23) Plan a solo artist date once a week to remind yourself that productivity includes pleasure.
24) Nature is your friend. And low-key free therapist.
25) Move based on your joy not other people’s judgment.
26) Time is your most finite resource.
27) Intuition is never wrong. Follow the feeling with your entire being.
28) Manifestation only works if you work.
29) Never let anyone make you feel inferior, period.
30) If luck is preparation meeting opportunity, then always stay ready.
31) Never forget where you came from.
32) The sword is only as good as its master.
33) Greatness is earned. There’s always a price to pay: Attention.
—

Half day wellness retreat with @nike and @rebelsport
We condensed our retreat into a morning in Sydney & the turn-out was beyond anything I could have imagined! MY BESTIE CAME TOO SO MY YEAR IS NOW COMPLETE. ✔️ ✔️ 

Everyone that came was gifted my favourite items from the new Nike range (actually in love with the chocolate Nike Zenvy leggings and the crop of my dreams).

I ran them through a juicy, twisty, challenging yoga flow, breathwork & meditation. 🧘🏽‍♀️ 

May have personally gotten a little emotional talking about what #feelyourall means to me

(See 👇🏽 for what Feel Your All means to me)

The guests then moved into the next room where Brit & I presented WFPB* on-the-go snacks & had an in-depth chat about the necessity of being prepared in order to fuel your training, busy life and physical & mental health

*Whole Food Plant Based 🥙 🌱🌵

The retreat closed with 1HR of meditative dance, silent-disco style. A room of women, letting go of fears of being seen, letting our hair out and shimmying, laughing, crying until our smiling muscles could no longer keep up.

FEEL YOUR ALL.🌞
To me, this phrase perfectly describes the way I live life.
To be fully present in each moment makes it possible for you to feel your all.
If you’re stuck worrying about the past or fretting the future - your mind is not capable of embracing the present moment.

To be fully present is a HARD TASK. 
It is no simple, easy feat.

In fact, I have been working on it for years & work on it every day.
I have learnt the best way to support this journey is to NOURISH yourself through every facet.

Nourish your brain with optimal sleep.

Nourish your gut, energy, & immune system with diverse nutrition.

Nourish your mental health with meditation/yoga/time alone.

Nourish your body with plenty of movement & recovery.

As you can see, all of these concept’s feed into one another, so start small& slowly work up. 

Somewhere along the line, you’ll look back with GRATEFULNESS that you chose to start this journey.

PAUSE.
Put down your devices.
Take a few slow breaths.
Name 3 things you’re grateful for.
Name 3 things around you that you consider beautiful or joyful 
💛

From @nikewomen :

“Women who run together, stay together ✌️”

That’s the goal for @native_women_running, who encourage Indigenous women across the country to honor their heritage by running as one. Members in Page, Arizona, say every run is an opportunity to connect with each other, their land and their ancestors.“ The feeling is different than when you’re running on your own. It’s almost like you were missing something that you didn’t know was missing, and now it’s all together,” says team leader @angels_ventures, of the Navajo Nation.

Between training runs, chill jogs and racing events, these women show up for each other through the finish line and beyond. What women keep you going? Let us know in the comments 👇 #FeelYourAll.

@boltchicago takes its athletes through Linear Periodization. Linear Periodization is where you increase intensity and decrease volume over a period of time. 

There are 4 phases in this program:

⚡️ Hypertrophy/Muscle Endurance
⚡️ Basic Strength
⚡️ Power

Linear Periodization is great for beginners and advanced athletes alike who want to build a solid strength foundation. 

It’s a powerful tool for breaking plateaus and almost always guarantees better outcomes long term 👌

This chapter is called, “Rebirth.” It’s my birthday today. It’s a time of reflection and recommitment to the ethos and events of the past year that changed my life, especially with the most epic campaign I could ever ask for, @nikewomen @nike Feel Your All. My mom is very proud.
—
Winning the day one by one, I took on an unorthodox entry level of mixed martial arts to understand and actualize my sense of happiness. My wholeness. I’ve never felt more completely myself than when I hold a staff, sword, shield, and other fun tactical things that awaken the power within. I must have been hiding for a while for big magic had to fight itself through me. I’ve meant it when I’ve said that martial arts saved me from myself, battling anxiety about who I was and what I wanted, to be driven by purpose instead of pretend. Martial arts is life. I understand it as a warrior and I always will.
—
I look in the mirror to nowadays and see different. Wiser and more wolf. My life has worked much better the less I resisted destiny and the more I opened my heart to show the world what’s inside. I judge less to feel more. I thank more to love much, much more. No limits. Just kisses from the stars and the little me who stubbornly held onto the hopes and dreams that the adult me is tasked to carry out to fulfillment for both of us. For all of us. I can assure you, as my life this past year is a true testament to this, that you are capable of far more than you allow yourself to believe. You’re a miracle in the making. You need to keep moving because the world needs you. You need you. Never, ever give up on yourself.
—
Cheers to another year around the sun. I wish you all faith and miracles. Thank you so much for being a part of my hero’s journey. #FEELYOURALL Big love for the Swoosh babes for making my dreams come true.

After #Nike enlisted a biological man to advertise a #bra and #leggings, many people expressed their disapproval by leaving comments on Nike's #Instagram account. But Nike posted a comment of its own, telling people to be nice while also threatening to delete comments "that are not in the spirit of a diverse and inclusive community."

#GOWOKEGOBROKE

Earlier this week, Autogynephiliac #DylanMulvaney, who identifies as a #transgender 'woman', posted content in which he was sporting the women's apparel: "Home for a moment and leaning into cozy workout wear life with @NikeWomen‘s newest #Zenvy leggings and Alate bra! They’re so comfortable and buttery soft, perfect for workouts and everyday wear! #feelyourall #teamnike #NikePartner," #Mulvaney wrote in an Instagram post that has been labeled as a paid partnership...

Nike's move to have a man advertise women's clothing sparked backlash, with people making their disapproval known on Nike's Instagram page.

"I have five grandsons that I won’t be buying Nike products for anymore. I'll buy from companies that support women," one person wrote in a comment on a Nike post advertising a shoe.

"I don't support misogyny or delusions. No more Nike for me," someone else wrote.

"I am never buying your products again! Go woke go broke!" another commenter declared.

Nike dropped a message of its own in the comments section, declaring, "You are an essential component to the success of your community! We welcome comments that contribute to a positive and constructive discussion: Be kind," Nike wrote, adding, "Be inclusive," and "Encourage each other." The company wrote that, "Hate speech, bullying, or other behaviors that are not in the spirit of a diverse and inclusive community will be deleted."

Anheuser-Busch also recently came under heavy criticism for having Mulvaney advertise #BudLight and for sending Mulvaney a beer can with his face on it.

빨리 달려야 할 것 같아서, 부상이 생길까봐 저어한다

있는 그대로의 환경이 줄 수 있는 최적의 컨디션을 확보하고 싶었다
근데 결국 비가 왔다 하핫
하지만 거의 노쇼없이 참석을 해주셨고, 답사 할때마다 사실은 그날 그날의 선물같은 자연과 컨디션이 달랐기에 힘을 냈다

LIFE LATELY//: When it comes to my wellness and the routines I’m trying to cultivate, I’ve been very intentional about the ways in which I can find some softness in the moments.
.
.
Our wellness is so intersectional… and impacts how we feel. This week I had the opportunity to help others lean into the softness of it all and slow it all down. Slow movements, deep breaths and stillness was the theme. We worked through, tight hips, sore shoulders and met and embraced our bodies with kindness and compassion… because meeting yourself where you are at is such a beautiful thing. 
.
.
Still smiling from teaching at Nike Style Lounge NYC. Thank you @nikewomen for providing me with an opportunity to share this practice. A practice that celebrates the beauty of softness, slowing down, resting. A practice that reminds us our bodies are our friends and treating ourselves with compassion is the most liberating thing we can do. 
.

Get you a girl who can be both: A baddie and a goof. I turned 33 on March 29 and reached my anniversary of mixed martial arts on April 2nd. Can I get an amen! These are the blessed 33 things I’ve learned, and I hope that you do too:
—
1) Honor the process.
2) Mental wellness is a martial art: Train your brain as much as your body.
3) Commitment is sexy.
4) Doing the work is also very, very sexy.
5) Flowers need sun, water, and air. So do you to grow in your own time.
6) Everything always works out for you even if it doesn’t seem like it on the outside.
7) Find your people, the ones who get your weird and your wins.
8) Not everything is a competition. It’s a learning lesson.
9) Strike when the iron is hot. The moment matters.
10) The art of war is the art of peace.
11) With anything in life, it’s important to know your style and own it from the bones.
12) Being teachable is more attractive than being right.
13) Everyone operates at their own speed, so drive accordingly.
14) Be kind is badass.
15) Allow life to surprise you as you stay the course.
16) Forgive, but don’t forget.
17) “Thank you” is “I love you” too.
18) You are your biggest cheerleader.
19) Passion is non-negotiable when it comes to true purpose.
20) Find small goals to stay engaged in the big one.
21) Expertise comes in the most unlikeliest of places.
22) Stay grateful. Gratitude is magnitude.
23) Plan a solo artist date once a week to remind yourself that productivity includes pleasure.
24) Nature is your friend. And low-key free therapist.
25) Move based on your joy not other people’s judgment.
26) Time is your most finite resource.
27) Intuition is never wrong. Follow the feeling with your entire being.
28) Manifestation only works if you work.
29) Never let anyone make you feel inferior, period.
30) If luck is preparation meeting opportunity, then always stay ready.
31) Never forget where you came from.
32) The sword is only as good as its master.
33) Greatness is earned. There’s always a price to pay: Attention.
—

Half day wellness retreat with @nike and @rebelsport
We condensed our retreat into a morning in Sydney & the turn-out was beyond anything I could have imagined! MY BESTIE CAME TOO SO MY YEAR IS NOW COMPLETE. ✔️ ✔️ 

Everyone that came was gifted my favourite items from the new Nike range (actually in love with the chocolate Nike Zenvy leggings and the crop of my dreams).

I ran them through a juicy, twisty, challenging yoga flow, breathwork & meditation. 🧘🏽‍♀️ 

May have personally gotten a little emotional talking about what #feelyourall means to me

(See 👇🏽 for what Feel Your All means to me)

The guests then moved into the next room where Brit & I presented WFPB* on-the-go snacks & had an in-depth chat about the necessity of being prepared in order to fuel your training, busy life and physical & mental health

*Whole Food Plant Based 🥙 🌱🌵

The retreat closed with 1HR of meditative dance, silent-disco style. A room of women, letting go of fears of being seen, letting our hair out and shimmying, laughing, crying until our smiling muscles could no longer keep up.

FEEL YOUR ALL.🌞
To me, this phrase perfectly describes the way I live life.
To be fully present in each moment makes it possible for you to feel your all.
If you’re stuck worrying about the past or fretting the future - your mind is not capable of embracing the present moment.

To be fully present is a HARD TASK. 
It is no simple, easy feat.

In fact, I have been working on it for years & work on it every day.
I have learnt the best way to support this journey is to NOURISH yourself through every facet.

Nourish your brain with optimal sleep.

Nourish your gut, energy, & immune system with diverse nutrition.

Nourish your mental health with meditation/yoga/time alone.

Nourish your body with plenty of movement & recovery.

As you can see, all of these concept’s feed into one another, so start small& slowly work up. 

Somewhere along the line, you’ll look back with GRATEFULNESS that you chose to start this journey.

PAUSE.
Put down your devices.
Take a few slow breaths.
Name 3 things you’re grateful for.
Name 3 things around you that you consider beautiful or joyful 
💛

Stills from one of the @nikewomen campaigns I was fortunate enough to be a part of. This project really taught me a lot. I’m thankful that I got to spend time with these women it was truly inspiring.

From @nikewomen :

“Women who run together, stay together ✌️”

That’s the goal for @native_women_running, who encourage Indigenous women across the country to honor their heritage by running as one. Members in Page, Arizona, say every run is an opportunity to connect with each other, their land and their ancestors.“ The feeling is different than when you’re running on your own. It’s almost like you were missing something that you didn’t know was missing, and now it’s all together,” says team leader @angels_ventures, of the Navajo Nation.

Between training runs, chill jogs and racing events, these women show up for each other through the finish line and beyond. What women keep you going? Let us know in the comments 👇 #FeelYourAll.

An accurate depiction of me thinking about what I want to program in the next Hypertrophy Phase 🤔

@boltchicago takes its athletes through Linear Periodization. Linear Periodization is where you increase intensity and decrease volume over a period of time. 

There are 4 phases in this program:

⚡️ Hypertrophy/Muscle Endurance
⚡️ Basic Strength
⚡️ Power

Linear Periodization is great for beginners and advanced athletes alike who want to build a solid strength foundation. 

It’s a powerful tool for breaking plateaus and almost always guarantees better outcomes long term 👌

Stop exercising and start training with a purpose! See you in class 💪

This chapter is called, “Rebirth.” It’s my birthday today. It’s a time of reflection and recommitment to the ethos and events of the past year that changed my life, especially with the most epic campaign I could ever ask for, @nikewomen @nike Feel Your All. My mom is very proud.
—
Winning the day one by one, I took on an unorthodox entry level of mixed martial arts to understand and actualize my sense of happiness. My wholeness. I’ve never felt more completely myself than when I hold a staff, sword, shield, and other fun tactical things that awaken the power within. I must have been hiding for a while for big magic had to fight itself through me. I’ve meant it when I’ve said that martial arts saved me from myself, battling anxiety about who I was and what I wanted, to be driven by purpose instead of pretend. Martial arts is life. I understand it as a warrior and I always will.
—
I look in the mirror to nowadays and see different. Wiser and more wolf. My life has worked much better the less I resisted destiny and the more I opened my heart to show the world what’s inside. I judge less to feel more. I thank more to love much, much more. No limits. Just kisses from the stars and the little me who stubbornly held onto the hopes and dreams that the adult me is tasked to carry out to fulfillment for both of us. For all of us. I can assure you, as my life this past year is a true testament to this, that you are capable of far more than you allow yourself to believe. You’re a miracle in the making. You need to keep moving because the world needs you. You need you. Never, ever give up on yourself.
—
Cheers to another year around the sun. I wish you all faith and miracles. Thank you so much for being a part of my hero’s journey. #FEELYOURALL Big love for the Swoosh babes for making my dreams come true.

Lady Dust Devil Jocelyn Melendez was clutch at the plate with runners on base today, driving in four on two hits to lead Santa Cruz  past St. Augustine 18-3.  Melendez drove in runs on a double in the first and a double in the second, Melendez also scored three runs for SC.

Rhaylyn Tarango took the win for Santa Cruz. The senior allowed four hits and three runs over four innings, striking out four and walking zero.

Isabela De La Torre was in the circle for the Lady Wolves. The righty lasted four innings, allowing 14 hits and 18 runs while striking out one.

The Lady Dust Devils scattered 14 hits in the game. Tatiyana Reyes led SC with three hits followed by Ylianna Velazco, Melendez, Emilee Brown, and Tarango each with two hits. Izzy Davis, Elyana Garza & Mio Banda added one hit each. 

SC had six stolen bases, Mariah Davis & Aaliyah Bojorquez led Santa Cruz with two stolen bases, Reyes & I Davis each added one.

#10 Abril | 🌍 Que el pádel es una deporte en pleno desarrollo y crecimiento es uno de esos mantras que, repetido en infinidad de ocasiones, ha dejado de ser llamativo para convertirse casi en cotidiano. 

Pero, tras él, existe una expansión imparable que sitúa a esta modalidad deportiva como una de las que más progresa a nivel mundial.

👉🏻 El pádel, entre los deportes que más crece 

Ya en 2021 el pádel se situó como el deporte con mayor crecimiento a nivel mundial. 

Según un estudio realizado por Monitor Deloitte y Playtomic, el deporte de la pala apuntaba para 2025-26 a su ruptura total en el plano internacional.

En la actualidad la Federación Internacional de Pádel (FIP) recoge en su página web unas cifras significativas. 

Con presencia en más de 90 países y una masa de jugadores superior a 25 millones, su evolución es ya seguida de cerca. 

Pero, hay quien apunta más alto.
Según la guía especializada Padel Lands, que funciona a la par como buscador, en la actualidad se podría ya practicar pádel en 115 países estando, incluso, presente en los cinco continentes. 

La isla de San Martín, Kenia, Curaçao, Indonesia, Hawai o Irak son algunos de los escenarios más llamativos.

𝙏𝙝𝙚 𝙄𝙢𝙢𝙤𝙧𝙩𝙖𝙡𝙞𝙨𝙩𝙨⁠
⁠
The basis of this book is that four siblings visit a fortune teller and she gives them each the date of their death. She does this privately, and they don't tell each other, they just all go home and try to deal with it the best they can given they're all teenagers or younger.⁠
⁠
The rest of the book follows the siblings one at a time as they grow up and face their incoming death dates, all of them handling it in a different way. Some of the siblings completely ignore what the fortune teller said, some of them completely believe it, some of them make choices "just in case" she's right.⁠
⁠
It was an interesting read, mostly in exploring fate vs. free will and how knowing the date of our death could help us live our life to the fullest or to shrink down and stay safe.⁠
⁠
I will say I didn't love the siblings, and after the first death prophecy came true, I was less interested in reading the rest of the book, so it took a few days to finish. If you like complex family sagas or exploratory fiction, this book is for you. Otherwise... don't push yourself to read it.⁠
⁠
Rating: ⭐️⭐️⭐️⁠

I wrapped up #TheGoldenSpoon by Jessa Maxwell & it as Book Pages coined it, it was the perfect blend of The Great British Bake Off & Knives Off! • • six amateur bakers have just arrived at Grafton Manor to compete in Bake Week, hosted by famous baker, Betsy Martin. But Bake Week is more than just a competition to Betsy, it’s her legacy & Grafton Manor, her family home. But as the conception begins, things start to go awry. Small acts of sabotage at first. But when a dead body is discovered, it’s clear The Golden Spoon prize is a prize worth killing for. • • • As someone who loves watching baking shows (& baking), this novel was right up my alley! And the setting of an old family estate? Yes, please. The story was a bit of a slow burn, the dead body didn’t show up until 3/4 of the way through. The majority of the story was just getting to know the characters & their motives for being there. And then of course there was the sub-plot mystery which was definitely a good one! Overall, I’d recommend it. I give it ⭐️⭐️⭐️. #bookstagram #booklove #booklife #bibliophile #librariansofinstagram

What is Runners Helping Runners (RHR)? 

RUNNERS HELPING RUNNERS is a global campaign by @nike to support the running community around the world.  In 2021, the project was launched with Olympic gold medelist and world record holder for Marathon; @kipchogeeliud playing his part as the boss sitting in a command centre where he monitors, share insight and answer questions from runners all over the world. (Give a ❤️ in the comment if you’ve watched the video)

Last year, in anticipation of Tokyo Marathon, Nike launched of RHR Tokyo Edition, a week before the event.  The program is led by @suguru_osako, supported by a network of Nike coaches, athletes and runners across Japan. (Link to the video at my bio)

Nike’s RHR campaign continues to provide support for the global running community.  In Malaysia, the campaign started with the first session, A Run in The Park held in July last year, hosted by @antzcolony after celebrating #Nike50 at Bukit Jalil a month before.

Since then RHR has continued to provide runners with invaluable support and guidance, offering monthly sessions filled with running tips, knowledge sharing, recovery techniques and nutrition advise as well as safety awareness for her.  Whether you are a seasoned runner or just starting out, RHR offers something for everyone.

Looking ahead to the Q2 of 2023, lead by 5 captains (@hushmo @adzshah @wando_acrc @kin_fitjournal and myself), #RunnersHelpingRunners MY is exploring new ways to engage with the running community, committed to helping runners stay motivated, inspired and on track to achieve their goals. Come and join us!

How to join RHR Nike Live Experience session?
• Download NRC app
• Sign up and keep your NRC app active to receive notification/ update of the upcoming session.

See you in April!

Here’s the truth about self-confidence. 

.

It’s NOT walking in the room thinking you’re better than anyone else.

. 

It’s NOT a skill that can be learned or something you’re born with.

. 

It’s NOT being the most attractive person.

. 

It’s NOT having the most expensive things.

. 

It’s simply fully accepting your weird, flawed self and allowing others to be themselves without putting them above or beneath you. 

. 

I used to think I had to act in a certain way to be accepted or validated and that stressed me out trying to create a character who I knew I wasn’t. 

. 

Like how most people operate right now whether they’re conscious about it or unconscious. 

. 

It’s like walking on eggshells not trying to say the wrong thing, or worrying too much about how that shirt or dress looks on you, or overanalyzing about what people might think of you. 

. 

What I’ve learned is that if you lack confidence, it has nothing to do with the outside world or how they make you feel whether you get triggered by what someone said or what you watch on a television show. 

. 

It has everything to do with you not knowing how to manage your own thoughts, emotions, and actions but allowing the outside world to do that for you. 

. 

Once you fully understand this, you’ll come to realize that everyone’s just trying their best in their life situation to fulfill their own made-up character due to their life experiences, cultural conditioning, media consumption, and opinions from family/friends. 

. 

And then you become more concerned about other peoples well-being instead of being so self-conscious on how other people view you. 

. 

That being said self-confidence is an internal job, NOT external. 🧬⚡️
.

It aspires to understand and highlight the complex relationship the black woman has developed with her hair in a Euro-norming country. Necessarily, the book project interrogates notions of beauty, femininity, desirability, racism, opportunity, and social mobility in a land that touts its “racial democracy.”

✨Miss Mandys Motivational Moment ✨

Confessions from a car cash. 🚘🧼

The truth is that I am excited to end a chapter of my life and begin a new one. 

Although at times it’s lonely in compared to what I’ve had being married for almost two decades, it makes up for it with me actually at being at peace for the first time in a long time and not negotiating with myself to appease others in the name of love. 

I will no longer dishonor myself, especially in the name of love.

During the last seven months I have learned a lot about myself and I’ve grown in ways that I never knew that I could and/or would have to. 

I’ve learned how to honor myself and speak my truth even at the risk of loss, I’ve had to protect and provide for my kids solely on my own, I have made apologies and taken accountability for hurting others feelings not knowing at the time on how navigate trough pure chaos in a better manner at times. 

I have better and healthier boundaries and I have been letting go of attachments to people, places and things that don’t serve me and that I feel that I’ve outgrown while making no apologies at the same time nor trying to hurt anyone feelings intentionally and I’ve done so with grace, grit and gratitude for it all and know they are all opportunities to grow. 

I do still and will always send love to all my loved ones of current and the past. 

Meanwhile this is “My Time” and I am getting in touch with my highest and truest self all the while manifesting the best life I ever could have imagined for me and my kids, family, friends, team, community and in turn the world.

Therefore when the time is right I will be ready and aligned to meet and to love full who it is that’s meant for me in future chapters of my life! 

Until then I’m currently dating myself and truly loving myself, all while not tolerating shitty behaviors and excuses.

One Love / Much Love,

- Miss Mandy 💋

【生地製造の革命児？　ナイキが創造する新しい服作り】

①ナイキフォワード

ナイキが新たに開発した生地の製造方法。ニット編物や織物とは全く異なる方法で生地を作ることで、エネルギー使用量を大幅に削減することに成功したそうです！

②ナイキフォワードの凄さとは？

通常、生地を作る上では紡糸や編みなどの工程をふみますが、ナイキフォワードでは繊維を何層にも重ねて、専用針を刺しながら圧縮するニードルパンチという技術を用いて繊維から直接素材を作っています。

これにより生地の製造工程を大幅に短縮でき、従来の製造方法と比べて二酸化炭素の排出量を75%削減できるんです！

③ 製造の構造を変える

リサイクル素材等を活用するだけではなく生産工程そのものにメスを入れてエネルギー使用量を大幅に削減したナイキフォワード。

持続可能なファッション産業を実現するためには、サステナブル素材の開発だけでなく、持続可能な生産体制の整備など様々なアプローチが必要であることを教えてくれる取り組みですね！

Tak mau kalah dengan kompetitor yang menerapkan strategi keberlanjutan, baik di lini produk atau manajerialnya, produsen apparel raksasa dunia, Nike, meluncurkan program baru keberlanjutan korporasinya.

Dinamai Nike Forward, yang merupakan program inovatif yang menitikberatkan pada proses untuk pembuatan busana yang berpeformansi tinggi sekaligus mengurangi dampak buruknya pada lingkungan. Mengutip dari Inhabitat, sebagai hasil dari proses tersebut, Nike meluncurkan salah satu koleksi hoodie elegan berwarna kelabu.

Aaron Heiser, Vice President Global Apparel Product Merchandising, NIKE, Inc., menjelaskan bahwa pihaknya percaya cara ini berpotensi untuk memberikan pemahaman baru tentang material dan apparel yang positif.

“Ini adalah inovasi apparel terbaik Nike sejak Dri-Fit 30 tahun yang lalu, yang saat itu memberikan tranformasi baru pada lini produk, seperti halnya seri ‘Air’ dan ‘Flyknit’ pada deretan koleksi alas kaki,” katanya.

Hal yang menjadi istimewa dari Nike Forward adalah kemampuannya untuk mengurangi 75% jejak karbon selama proses produksi dibandingkan produk Nike konvensional (knit fleece). Lebih jauh, proses pembuatan produk dipersingkat di mana serat diubah menjadi material tekstil dengan menggunakan metode ‘needle-punch’. 

Ini pada praktiknya menghilangkan beberapa tahapan produksi seperti pada produk Nike yang lain. Setiap tahapan yang hilang berarti mengurangi pemakaian energi, air, dan tenaga manusia sebagai bagian dari proses. 

Nike sudah mengambil cara pendekatan produksi yang lebih minimalis lewat desain ultra simpel, berupa hoodie yang menanggalkan pewarna dan risleting tambahan (yang biasanya mengandung plastik) serta saku yang bergaya “raw cut pocket”. Lalu sentuhan akhir hoodie kekinian ini terbuat dari 70% bahan daur ulang, yang juga berkontribusi pada pencapaian tujuan sirkular dari perusahaan.

Untuk informasi selengkapnya klik www.majalahcsr.id

Sustainable Fashion | Have you seen this kind of fabric?
Do you know what the clothes you wear are made of?

As a giant in sports apparel industry, NIKE has been taking practical actions to fulfill its commitment and obligation on the road of sustainable development.

NIKE FORWARD is the most important clothing innovation technology of NIKE since DRI-FIT. It practices the concept of sustainable environmental protection through the new environment-friendly fabric.
NIKE FORWARD is the innovation of NIKE's research and development team, which lasted more than five years. Instead OF the TRADITIONAL knitting OR weaving process, THE production process is reduced, and the fiber is directly turned into a textile by the needling process, which also means less energy consumption. In addition, the finished products are made of partially recycled materials.
The concept of sustainability runs through the design of the whole series of products, abandoning the traditional dyeing steps, no decorative accessories, and using uncut pockets; In addition to simplifying the process, water is also saved. The material's carbon footprint is reduced by an average of 75 percent compared to conventional knitted wool.👣
And Nike Forward products come with no zippers, shoulder straps or extra embellishments, making the clothing easier to recycle♻️.

Sounds technical, and it is! They have already obtained a patent for it. With products having no additional bits, such as zippers or dyes, Nike believes they can reduce the carbon footprint of the manufacturing process by 75%. Getting patents for these processes is essential before any launch, so it’s good to get them in early! Going fordward means going towards zero 

Fashion is so fast-paced, that sometimes there isn’t time for real innovation. @Nike has been playing a bigger and bigger role in fashion in recent years, probably because it is a leader in innovation and has built a culture around it. To put that into perspective #NikeForward material has seen 5+ years of research and development behind it, and it’s a real game changer that challenges the extractive consequences of fashion to a more circular one. Nike Forward is their most significant apparel innovation since Dri-Fit, responding to that concern by re-setting the way we think about fleece. Now with Nike Forward significantly reduced the carbon footprint of its first gen material by 75% by creating a new cycle that turns fiber (with a diverse range of layers, including industrial and post-consumer waste) directly to textile through needle-punch as opposed to the process of multistage (spin yarn, knit, cut, sew and more). 
Fewer steps means less energy consumption. Looking at the beloved hoodie silhouette, forgoes embellishments and dyes, favoring raw cut pickets and zero water usage. Made without zippers, aglets, or extra trims, also makes it easier for the garments to be recycled. Nike Forward is creating a new aesthetic in the process that sees both performance standards and fashion transforms the way we see and where wear clothes.

#MINDLYINSPIRATIONS / Nike Forward：具有顛覆意義的創新平台

世界各地的運動員都意識到：氣候變化 — 將會是影響運動表現的障礙。Nike Forward是Nike自Dri-Fit以來最重要的服裝創新科技，通過重新定義我們對針織絨布面料的認知來回應運動員們遇到的問題。Nike Forward摒棄了傳統的針織和梭織工藝，通過創新改造針刺機的運用為服裝製造帶來了顛覆性改變，目的是製造具有可持續性的優質產品。
 
Nike服裝創新部門副總裁Carmen Zolman表示：「Nike Forward給人特別的感覺，沿自其本身就與眾不同。它並非傳統針織或梭織產品，而是一種能大幅降低碳排放的全新材料，從而促使我們進一步探索服裝護理方式。」

Nike Forward是研發團隊歷時5年多的創新成果。摒棄傳統的針織或梭織工藝，通過減少步驟取代過往繁複的製作流程：紡紗、編織、切割、縫製等，以針刺工藝將纖維直接變成紡織品；更精簡的工藝步驟亦意味著更少的能源消耗，其碳排放量大幅少於Nike傳統起絨面料；在材料密度方面，Nike Forward亦相較傳統針織絨布更輕。此外，成品更採用部分再生材料製成。

Old project: Nike Pegasus Editorial page 2 (Part. 1 of 3)
\
\
Another student design project done at the very end of 2022, and is based off of Nike’s “Never Done Iterating: Pegasus: Runnings Workhorse” story from the Department of Nike Archives website.
\
This project started with creating the outline illustration of the Pegasus shoe and became the base for the collage piece. I wanted to show the five distinct years seen in the Nike story and make it easier to identify and relate each year to its respective shoe and information. So as best as I could, I chose parts of each shoe that seemed unique to its specific version. 
\ 
The most challenging part was figuring out how to relate each piece of the collage to its correct year and information. Overall, the layout was pretty busy and adding more elements to “connect” the collage and info came with visibility and legibility concerns. Eventually, I settled on using the silhouette of the shoe with a highlight of the relevant year, sort of like a legend used in a map or diagram. 
\

I have been STUCK!

For weeks, I have been hyper-fixating in a couple of areas in my business. 

You know those feelings of self-doubt, and insecurity that slowly creep into our minds and begin choking the positivity out.

I have been having them.

“I can’t post this”

Why not? It’s what you, my potential client, may need.

“This is not perfect enough”

Is it really not? Or am I overthinking it?

PSST, I AM overthinking it.

This slow and dark process then leaks into other areas of life.

My workouts suffer. My meal planning and prepping suffers. 

And the hole I am in just gets deeper.

So today, I got myself out by using the tools I have.

I took a long shower and made time to take care of my skin and hair.

I went to the gym and had a successful workout.

I did my business tasks for the day.

And in return, productivity was high, my emails are cleared out (AND read in their entirety), my muscles feel SO happy, and I overheard some rather nice things being said about me in the gym.

How’s that for a confidence boost???

If you are feeling stuck, know that you have all of the tools you need to save yourself.

TAKE the long shower.

Go to the gym and do a routine you enjoy.

Complete a single task you have been putting off, and start with the easiest one.

And when you’re finished, relax knowing that you saved yourself!
